clearGlobalNets(25.10)                                  clearGlobalNets(25.10)

Name
       clearGlobalNets - Resets the logical power net connection

Syntax
         clearGlobalNets [-help]

       Resets  the  logical  power net connection. It also clears all the tie-
       high and tie-low nets logical power net connection.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the clearGlobalNets command usage.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man clearGlobalNets

Examples
       If the logical connectivity of a VDD pin is set with VDD!  power  nets,
       VSS  pin  with  VSS!  and so on using the globalNetConnect command, the
       clearGlobalNets command will clear or undo all this logical power  nets
       connectivity. Refer to the commands below:

       globalNetConnect VDD! -pin VDD -override

       globalNetConnect VSS! -pin VSS -override

       clearGlobalNets

Related Information
       Power Planning and Routing chapter in the Innovus User Guide.

